job_description:
&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ready to be pushed beyond what you think you’re capable of?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Coinbase, our mission is to increase economic freedom in the world. It’s a massive, ambitious opportunity that demands the best of us, every day, as we build the emerging onchain platform — and with it, the future global financial system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To achieve our mission, we’re seeking a very specific candidate. We want someone who is passionate about our mission and who believes in the power of crypto and blockchain technology to update the financial system. We want someone who is eager to leave their mark on the world, who relishes the pressure and privilege of working with high caliber colleagues, and who actively seeks feedback to keep leveling up. We want someone who will run towards, not away from, solving the company’s hardest problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.coinbase.com/mission&quot;&gt;work culture&lt;/a&gt; is intense and isn’t for everyone. But if you want to build the future alongside others who excel in their disciplines and expect the same from you, there’s no better place to be.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While many roles at Coinbase are remote-first, we are not remote-only. In-person participation is required throughout the year. Team and company-wide offsites are held multiple times annually to foster collaboration, connection, and alignment. Attendance is expected and fully supported.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Join Coinbase&#39;s Marketing Events team as an intern and gain hands-on experience supporting the planning, execution, and measurement of our key marketing events from owned and operated experiences through to industry conferences and product launches. This role provides a unique opportunity to dive deep into the world of event and experiences, while learning how events support go-to-market strategies, product launches, and brand awareness efforts within the world of crypto. We&#39;re looking for someone passionate about crypto and excited to align with Coinbase’s cultural tenets of clear communication, effective execution, and a customer-first approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll be doing (ie. job duties):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute event strategies and project management for upcoming events + experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create event materials such as email invitations, presentations, project plans and event surveys.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with product marketing, sales, and design teams to ensure event activations align with broader marketing goals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping to track event performance metrics, gather post-event feedback, and contribute to post-event recap reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support key event operations such as finance, security and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for in you (ie. job requirements):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Interested in cryptocurrency, Web3, or fintech and willing to learn.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills, along with a collaborative mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Attention to detail and a desire to work in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to haves:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Familiarity with basic marketing concepts or coursework related to marketing, business, or finance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Some experience with research, data collection, or analysis (e.g., through academic projects).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Knowledge of social media platforms (ie. Discord, Telegram, X, Youtube, IG) and tools such as Google Sheets, Docs, or similar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job #: P73656&lt;/p&gt;
